">5. New developments enable new applications.</h2> <p style=3D"padding:0; =
margin:0 0 15px 0;"> Developments in computer vision and speech and voice (=
=E2=80=9Ceyes and ears=E2=80=9D) technology help drive the creation of new =
products and services that can make personalized, custom-sized clothing, dr=
ive autonomous harvesting robots, or provide the logic for proficient chatb=
ots. Work on robotics (=E2=80=9Carms and legs=E2=80=9D) and autonomous vehi=
cles is compelling and closer to market.</p> <p style=3D"padding:0; margin:=
0 0 15px 0;">There=E2=80=99s also a new wave of startups targeting =E2=80=
=9Ctraditional data=E2=80=9D with new AI and automation technologies. This =
includes text (new NLP and NLU solutions; chatbots), time series and tempor=
al data, transactional data, and logs. And both traditional enterprise soft=
ware vendors and startups are rushing to build AI applications that target =
specific industries or domains. This is in line with findings in a recent <=
a style=3D"text-decoration:underline; color:#ee0000;" href=3D
"http://link.oreilly.com/P000Q2rFWM0dWS0L0FoSuV0" target=3D"_blank"
>McKinsey survey</a>: enterprises are using AI in areas where they=E2=80=99=
ve already invested in basic analytics. </p> </td>=20
</tr>=20
