">6. Handling fairness=E2=80=94working from the premise that all data has b=
uilt-in biases.</h2> <p style=3D"padding:0; margin:0 0 15px 0;"> Taking a c=
ue from the software quality assurance world (which assumes that bugs exist=
 in software and need to be fixed), those working on AI models need to assu=
me their data has built-in or systemic bias and other issues and that forma=
l processes are needed to detect, correct, and address those issues. Detect=
ing bias and ensuring fairness doesn=E2=80=99t come easy and is most effect=
ive when subject to review and validation from a diverse set of perspective=
s.</p> <p style=3D"padding:0; margin:0 0 15px 0;">That means building inten=
tional diversity=E2=80=94cognitive diversity, socioeconomic diversity, cult=
ural diversity, and physical diversity=E2=80=94into the processes used to d=
etect unfairness and bias to help improve the process and mitigate the risk=
 of missing something critical. </p> </td>=20
</tr>=20
